# SumelaOS mirror targets (COMMITTED — team-wide).
#
# Most IDEs read AGENTS.md (or a thin pointer to it) and need NO mirror. But some
# weaker models skip "read the canonical file" directives, so a few IDE entrypoints
# must carry the body of `.sumela/sumela-prompt.md` VERBATIM. Rather than maintain
# that by hand, list those mirror files here (one path per line, relative to repo
# root) and run `scripts/sync-mirrors.sh` to keep them in sync. Pre-commit + CI run
# `sync-mirrors.sh --check` to fail on drift.
#
# Each listed file must contain a marker block; `sync-mirrors.sh` only rewrites the
# content BETWEEN the markers (your IDE-specific frontmatter/wrapper outside is kept):
#
#   <!-- SUMELA-MIRROR:BEGIN -->
#   <!-- SUMELA-MIRROR:END -->
#
# `scripts/sync-mirrors.sh --init` scaffolds a listed file (with markers) if missing.
# (Do not put the literal text SUMELA-MIRROR:BEGIN/END inside sumela-prompt.md itself —
#  it would collide with the mirror markers.)
#
# IMPORTANT: a mirror is shared, so it MUST be committable — make sure its path is not
# gitignored. If you blanket-ignore `.claude/` (common for local Claude settings), either
# un-ignore the agents subdir (`!.claude/agents/`) or put the mirror elsewhere.
#
# To activate: copy this file to `.sumela/mirrors.conf` and uncomment/add your paths.
# Examples (uncomment the ones you actually use):
# .claude/agents/sumela-agent.md
# .opencode/agents/sumela.md
